newsitem.title: TUNISIA: Tunisian treasury note yield down.
newsitem.headline: Tunisian treasury note yield down.

text.p: The Tunisian Treasury on Tuesday said it sold 30 million dinars of three-year notes at its weekly auction on October 22, repaying maturing paper totalling 8.2 million dinars.
The three-year notes payable in equal annual tranches were at a 9.0625 percent yield, down from 9.1250 last week.
Banks bid for 129 million dinars of three- and five-year notes at between 9.0625 and 9.5 percent.
